Got it üëç thanks for clarifying.
Since you‚Äôre using ASP.NET GridView + simple-datatables.js, the header sometimes doesn‚Äôt render cleanly (extra <tr> or <th> wrappers). That causes DataTables not to style the header correctly.

By default, GridView adds <thead> only if UseAccessibleHeader="true" is set. Without it, the header is inside <tr> inside <table> without <thead>, which breaks simple-datatables.


---

‚úÖ Fix: Add these properties to your GridView

<asp:GridView ID="gvMeetings" runat="server" 
    CssClass="table table-bordered table-striped"
    AutoGenerateColumns="False"
    UseAccessibleHeader="true"
    HeaderStyle-BackColor="#f8f9fa"
    HeaderStyle-Font-Bold="true"
    GridLines="None">
    <Columns>
        <asp:BoundField DataField="MeetingID" HeaderText="Meeting ID" />
        <asp:BoundField DataField="MeetingTitle" HeaderText="Title" />
        <asp:BoundField DataField="MeetingDate" HeaderText="Date" DataFormatString="{0:MM/dd/yyyy}" />
        <asp:BoundField DataField="CreatedBy" HeaderText="Created By" />
        <asp:BoundField DataField="Status" HeaderText="Status" />
        <asp:BoundField DataField="Location" HeaderText="Location" />
        <asp:BoundField DataField="Remarks" HeaderText="Remarks" />
    </Columns>
</asp:GridView>


---

‚úÖ And in CodeBehind (after DataBind):

private void LoadMeetings()
{
    string connStr = ConfigurationManager.ConnectionStrings["DefaultConnection"].ConnectionString;

    using (SqlConnection conn = new SqlConnection(connStr))
    {
        using (SqlCommand cmd = new SqlCommand("sp_GetMeetings", conn))
        {
            cmd.CommandType = CommandType.StoredProcedure;
            SqlDataAdapter da = new SqlDataAdapter(cmd);
            DataTable dt = new DataTable();
            da.Fill(dt);

            gvMeetings.DataSource = dt;
            gvMeetings.DataBind();

            // Ensure GridView renders <thead> for DataTables
            if (gvMeetings.HeaderRow != null)
            {
                gvMeetings.HeaderRow.TableSection = TableRowSection.TableHeader;
            }
        }
    }
}


---

‚úÖ Why this works

UseAccessibleHeader="true" makes GridView output <thead> and <th> tags.

gvMeetings.HeaderRow.TableSection = TableRowSection.TableHeader; ensures the header row is moved inside <thead>.

simple-datatables.js now detects headers properly and applies sorting/search styling.



